    "summary": {
      "value": "Fight with two weapons of different categories."
    },
    "description": "<p>You may apply the benefits of <strong>two-weapon fighting</strong> (<strong>Core Rulebook</strong>, page <strong>69</strong>) to weapons belonging to different Categories, even if one is a <strong>melee</strong> weapon and the other is a <strong>ranged </strong>weapon (such as a <strong>dagger</strong> and a <strong>firearm</strong>, for instance).</p><p>As long as you have <strong>exactly two weapons equipped</strong> and they <strong>share no Categories with each other</strong>, you gain a +2 bonus to Defense and the <strong>second attack</strong> you perform during each of your turns deals 5 extra damage.</p>",
